Ophir Optronics Soars Most on Record on Newport Acquisition Bid

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-07-10T08:00:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/ophir-optronics-soars-most-on-record-on-newport-acquisition-bid.html
Ophir Optronics Ltd. (OPIR)  surged the most
on record after Newport Corp. agreed to buy the Israeli maker of
optical instruments for $230 million in cash, or $8.43 a share.  The shares soared 76 percent, the most since at least
February 1996 when Bloomberg began tracking the stock, to 26.30
shekels ($7.73) at 10:42 a.m. in Tel Aviv.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Susan Lerner  in Jerusalem at 
 Slerner2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler in Dubai at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  